OL,3,CThe Lancastria: What happened and why
OL,4,Cis the tragedy 'forgotten'?
OL,6,FThe Cunard ship - originally named
OL,7,FTyrrhenia - sailed scheduled routes
OL,8,Fbetween Liverpool and New York until
OL,9,F1932, before she was then used as a
OL,10,Fcruise ship in the Mediterranean and
OL,11,FNorthern Europe.
OL,13,FAs the Second World War broke out in
OL,14,FSeptember 1939, Lancastria was in the
OL,15,FBahamas. She was ordered to sail from
OL,16,FNassau to New York for refitting as
OL,17,Fshe had been requisitioned as a
OL,18,Ftroopship, becoming HMT Lancastria.
