OL,3,CThe Lancastria: What happened and why
OL,4,Cis the tragedy 'forgotten'?
OL,6,FWhile still at anchor, the ship was
OL,7,Fdive bombed by Nazi planes, and
OL,8,Fcapsized and sank within 20 minutes,
OL,9,Fkilling at least 4,000 people.
OL,11,FThe loss of life equates to more than
OL,12,Fthe Titanic and Lusitania combined.
OL,14,FThere were 2,477 survivors - with many
OL,15,Ftaken aboard other British and Allied
OL,16,Fevacuation vessels - the trawler HMT
OL,17,FCambridgeshire rescued 900.
OL,19,FWhy is not much known about it?
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
