OL,3,CThe Lancastria: What happened and why
OL,4,Cis the tragedy 'forgotten'?
OL,6,FPrime Minister, Winston Churchill,
OL,7,Fordered a blackout on media outlets
OL,8,Freporting on the tragedy, as the
OL,9,FBritish government feared it would
OL,10,Ffurther lower British morale, and
OL,11,Fprovide Germany with propaganda.
OL,13,FMedia outlets eventually reported on
OL,14,Fthe incident at the end of July,
OL,15,Faround five weeks after it happened,
OL,16,Falthough Churchill's D-Notice
OL,17,Fpreventing publication of official
OL,18,Fdocuments of evidence is not set to
OL,19,Fexpire until 2040.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/6
